{title: The Upper Room}
{artist: Hank Locklin |Country Gospel}
{composer: Written by Hank Locklin and Frank Peterson}

This is My body which is [D7]given for you
[A7]He delivers remembrance for the works you must [D7]do
He [G]then took the cup and gave [D7]thanks over it
He said this is My blood you must [G]drink every bit
It is shed for the many who will [D7]answer the call
To redeem falling mankind I gave them My [G]all

Tears fill my eyes [D7]there's no more to say
We all know the story of the [G]next day
They seized our dear Savior [D7]they mocked Him with scorn
[A7]Now to our Savior the kingdom was [D7]born

The [G]pieces of silver did [D7]Judas no good
He hung himself as [G]Christ knew he would
But the fingers of God [D7]wove into life's loom
The memory of promise in the upper [G]room